Step by Step Guide to Web Scraping

1. Inspect the HTML. Go the table and right-click "inspect element"

2. Load the required HTML packages
import requests ->

3. Request the HTML of the site
website_url = requests.get(‘https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Asian_countries_by_area’).text

4. Load the Beautiful Soup package
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
soup = BeautifulSoup(website_url,’lxml’)
print(soup.prettify())

5. find the table name you want to extract
My_table = soup.find(‘table’,{‘class’:’wikitable sortable’})

Now to extract all the links within <a>, we will use find_all().
links=My_table.findAll('a')
links

6. Extract the names from column 1
Countries = []
for link in links:
Countries.append(link.get('title'))


